title: EV Charger Grantee Quarterly Operation Reports

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, MD. Code Ann, Gen. Prov. ("GP) §§ 4-101-4-601, I hereby request the following records:

Grantee Quarterly Operation Reports for Q3, 2022 and Q4, 2022 for the DC Fast Chargers funded under the Electric Vehicle Infrastructure Program (EVIP), the Alternative Fuel Infrastructure Program (AFIP) and any other programs for DC Fast Chargers funded by MEA that have Grantee Quarterly Operation Reports.

If all or any part of this request is denied, I request that I be provided with a written explanation that includes the reason for the denial, the legal authority justifying the denial, and my appeal rights. If you determine that some portions of the requested records are exempt from disclosure, please provide me with the portions that can be disclosed.

I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. In the event that fees cannot be waived, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available.

Under GP § 4-203(b)(1), if a custodian determines that a record is responsive to a request and open to inspection, the custodian must produce the record “immediately” after receipt of the written request. An additional reasonable period “not to exceed 30 days” is available only where the additional period of time is required to retrieve the records and assess their status under the PIA. A custodian should not, however, wait the full 30 days to allow or deny access to a record if that amount of time is not needed to respond.

If access is to be granted, the record should be produced for inspection and copying promptly after the written request is evaluated. If it will take more than 10 working days to produce the requested records, the custodian must notify the requester, in writing or by email, of that fact. GP § 4-203(b)(2). The notification must be sent within the same 10-working-day time period and must indicate the amount of time needed to respond, the reason for the delay, and an estimate of the range of fees that may be charged.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within the time period prescribed in the statute.

Sincerely,

Lanny Hartmann

title: Library of Congress Statistics and Expenses (Library of Congress)

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Library of Congress Statistics and Expenses (Library of Congress)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Responsive records to:

1. A list of books acquired by the U.S. Library of Congress on February 5th, 2023, which have publication dates after the year 2019.

2. Library of Congress expenses report for the year 2021.

3. Book donations to the Library of Congress in the year 2021.

5. Objects found within book donations in the year 2022.

6. Monetary gifts (donations) made to the Library of Congress Literacy and Reading Programs in the year 2021.

7. Books in the rare book collection that were captured with multispectral imaging and processed with principal component analysis (PCA) in the year 2021.

8. Statistics regarding the difference between how many books were physically added to the Library of Congress and how many books were catalogued by the Library of Congress in the year 2021.

9. A list of travel and food expenses paid for by the James Madison Council of the Library of Congress in the year 2021.

I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

title: Law Enforcement Agencies Accessing the North Dakota Bureau of Criminal Investigation's Face Recognition System

communications.subject: North Dakota Open Records Law Request: Law Enforcement Agencies Accessing the North Dakota Bureau of Criminal Investigation's Face Recognition System
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the North Dakota Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

I would like to learn: 1) which local, state and national law enforcement agencies can currently submit probe photos to be run through the Bureau of Criminal Investigation's face recognition system, and 2) which law enforcement agencies actually submitted probe photos to the Bureau for a search from January 1, 2020 to the date of the most recently available data.

Please provide any lists, logs or datasets showing this information.  With regard to agencies that have submitted probe photos, please provide logs, lists or datasets describing, as available, the requesting organization, the number of requests made, the dates of the requests, and the number of requests granted.  If the Bureau maintains this information in an Excel spreadsheet, I request that the record be produced in this format.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Paul Tepper

title: IDHS

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: IDHS
communications.communication:

2) Documentation of all decision-making algorithms, fraud detection,, or predictive models that the agency currently uses (including those used as aids to human decision making). This documentation should include, where available: executive summaries of the algorithm/model's purpose, lists of the data sources, breakdowns of how the model weights various input data, descriptions of the statistical or machine learning techniques employed, the results of validation and accuracy testing, disparate impact studies, and algorithmic impact reports.
